article.headline: Arkansas to face Duke in tournament's title game
article.linkText: Balance scoring gets No. 15 Arkansas into Paradise Jam final
article.story:
CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Shameka Christon,
Rudy Vaden and Cara Wright each scored 13 points to lead Arkansas (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today; No. 17 Associated Press) past Hampton 78-41 at the Paradise Jam tournament Friday.

	   Arkansas (4-0) held Hampton (1-2) to just 19 percent shooting
from the field in the first half and 28 percent for the game.

	   Hampton had 25 turnovers.

	   India Lewis had 11 points for Arkansas.

	   Brendy Ellis led Hampton with 12 points.

In the championship game, Arkansas will face Duke.
